SCS 3-18 April 30th, 2015
    - This include the latest Vibration Tracking (VTK) release.

    - The VTK parameter changes are now automated between 200Hz,
    100Hz and  50Hz guide frequencies. This means you can just
    leave VTK running (but manually turn it off when you switch
    to Altair).

    - VTK is not yet released for Altair.

    - The attached new SCS status screen shows when VTK is on.
    The corresponding lag parameters will change automatically
    as you change the guide frequency.

    - VTK at 50Hz has longer convergence times which we'll work
    to improve.

    - The SCS PARK command will turn VTK OFF for you.

    - Turning ON the SCS Following will *NOT* turn VTK ON (since
    you're probably going to be tuning with Altair when you put
    the SCS into Follow mode).

    - Although P1 works with VTK, it's not yet qualified for LGS
    mode. That pretty much rules out using P1 for now unless
    there's a need for P1/NGS.

    - Since Gemini's commissioning we have been guiding by
    steering M2 at 1/2 the guiding sample rate. I.e., 200 Hz
    guiding moves M2 only 100 Hz. 100Hz guiding moves M2 only
    50Hz, etc. This is termed "Legacy Mode" guiding. The new SCS
    release supports full sample-rate guiding, so 200Hz guiding
    moves M2 at 200Hz. However, this mode is not yet qualified
    for operations. ENT-15 0685 has been submitted for this
    purpose. Until this work is finished Legacy Mode will be the
    default.

