SCS Version 3-12 -Jan 2015 mrippa

    In July 2014 an Engineering Night Test (ENT14 0587) demonstrated a prototype of the vibration
    tracking algorithm described in [1]. The test was largely successful and defined an SCS upgrade path to
    allow selective tracking and rejection of vibration originating from M1 and outside the bandwidth of
    the P2 wavefront sensor.

    One problem found during the ENT was an error in the frequency tracking caused by incorrect phase
    unwrapping which results in a limit cycle as shown in [1], sections 4.2.1.2 and 5.6.1. This SCS release
    corrects this bug but needs to be functionally verified on-sky during a new ENT (ENT14-0651).
    Additional features were also identified.
    Here is the list of features and issues regarding this release:
        1. New VTK specific EPICS records for distributed control requirements

        2. New VTK specific EPICS configuration and control screens (See section 2)

        3. New Synthetic Wave EPICS records for distributed control requirements.

        4. New Synthetic Wave EPICS configuration and control screens (See secton 2)
        
        5. VTK Phase unwrapping bug fix
        
        6. VTK Recycling Mode is added to support daytime engineering mode as described [1], section
5.5.

Reference: 
           [1] "H. Bonnet, Vibrations at Gemini", 2014
           [2] "M.Rippa, ENT-14_0651Results" ,2015



