SCS Version 3-10R1 - May 2009 Release
      1. Includes new tiptiltGuideLimitFactor and FocusGuideLimitFactor,
         which allows to be modified from the console. The default 
         value for both is 1.0.

SCS Version 3-10 - September 2008 Release
      1. Includes libraries for multi-node RM diagnostics. These are
         not normally run during nightly operations, but will be included
         in this release.

      2. Refactor initialize procedure without long delays between states.
         Solves INIT ending in error at the CEM and properly moves M2/XY
         to park positions without any user intervention.

      3. Includes interrupt cycle profiling to measure how long the
         fast-guide ISR takes to return to the SCS. This is helpful to
         know since the fast-guide interrupt process is asynchronous in
         the sense that there's nothing stopping the SCS from interrupting
         the CEM again while the last fast-guide ISR is executing. So this
         benchmark should always report fast-guide ISR completion times
         much less than 1ms. If they're ever reported in the several ms
         range there's danger of blowing the DOS stack: i.e., the ISR is
         not reentrant.

      4. Pseudo-guiding improvements to allow all engineers to safely
         execute this handy tool. Previously you had to configure this at a
         low level which was complicated. This is be controlled with a
         new EPICS screen guideSimulate.dl.

      5. Improvements to XY position plot. Includes:
         a) correct axid labels,
         b) proper range on the x-axis.
         c) Increased number of saved plot points from 1000 to 5000.

      6. New DM screen for Pseudo guiding control.

      7. New DM screen entry under tolerances for the XY Deadband.

      8. New feature to remotely set the XY Deadband. Implemented in
         the CAD tolerance routines.

      9. New feature to track the Position drift between microE's and Kamans


SCS Version 3-9 - Refactored the EventSystem Sections:
        - xycom.c   - Includes new task/ISR during chopping to listen
                      for interrupts coming from M2 InPosition.
                      Handler for said interrupt updates Event System
                      and modifies the Guide Gate appropriately.
        - control.c - New Guide Gate concept which turns ON|OFF 
                      'applyGuide' as determined from above 
                      interrupts.
        - testFunctions.c:
                      Includes new tasks for running a daytime guide 
                      simulator.

