SCS Version 34 - Now focus applied guide value is not automatically set to 
                 zero when the guide loop is turned off. 
                 A new command has been implemented "clear guide focus" to set 
                 to zero the focus applied guide value.

SCS Version 33 - A new feature implemented to handle initialization of TILT
                 system and XY positioner system. Also, a new version in 
                 CEM pc is also needed. Because, the new command XYINIT was
                 implemented to that software level. 

                 A park command now reaches the predefined position at the
                 first try.
                 At the same time, MOFFLOFF CEM command was removed from the 
                 PARK command, that means, after a park the offloader are still
                 ON.

                 A modification from Corinne in control.c file. 



                 Files modified:

                        control.c : Corinne's modification and added string 
                                CMD_INITXY to the commands list.

                        control.h : CMD_INITXY=59 added to the enumerated type.

                        house.c : CADinitXY function added to handle XYINIT 
                                command.

                        scs_st.stpp : Added the code to control XY Positioner
                                initialization process. Functions added 
                                startInitXY, waitForInitStartXY and
                                waitForInitCompletionXY.

                                Beside that, the park command is not turning 
                                OFF the offloader, MOFFLOFF command removed.
                                A new SNL state parkWaitForFineCoincedence 
                                created to permit the close loop movement
                                of actuators, before VEND and MEND commands.

                        showEngineering.c : Added CMD_INITXY command to the list        
                        utilities.h : defined Y_POSITION_LIMIT 6000.00. This
                                variable was used but not defined.
                
                                                                 




SCS Version 32 - Now it is possible to do closed loop focus when chopping -
                 Version used during the OSCIR run of the 1st to the 10th 
                 of February 2001
SCS Version 31 - Remember how we are flipping the demands in "readDemand"
                 so that dmd0 high means A and low means B (as input).
                 Well, now we have to do a second flip (in updateEventPage)
                 - you would like these two inversions would cancel each
                 other out, but such is not the case. 
               - Also now implement Corinne's idea of ensuring that 
                 ISR doesn't get MORE interrupts than the number of
                 semaphores it gives to xyIntHandler. Note: now that
                 DECS is not being toggled for each nod (and neither is
                 CHOP), there are no missed interrupts anymore - but 
                 leave this change in, just in case.

SCS Version 30 - Updates to xycom.c to accommodate timing of CHOP ON
                 command followed by the start of the ICS optical 
                 signals at some time, approx. 2 sec later. Uses new
                 globals to indicate chop "pending" condition and for
                 M2's response to CHOP ON.
               - Add values to SCSinit for PID control to be ON.

SCS Version 29 - New way of chopping and guiding. In processguides,
                 set applyGuide to TRUE when zernickes not identically zero.
               - cbaf/dbaf name change with changes to TCS
               - sync mask displayed on status dm
               - ring buffers in CEM and MCDSP are togglable via primitive
                 commands page.

SCS Version 28 - Changes related to getting chopping and guiding to work
                 from an externally sync'd STROBED ICS (OSCIR and signal
                 generator). A lot of files here. Xycom.c is new and right
                 now consists of the low-level driver routines and the
                 higher level chop control routines. It would be nice to
                 separate these two types of routines (moving the higher
                 level stuff up to chopControl.c), but it is not a priority,
                 only a nicety.

SCS Version 23-27 - Switchover to using instRelease with gemConfig to install
                 binaries and data files on scott:/gemini/scs/Vx-xx and vega:
                 /gemini/scs/Vx-xx
 
SCS Version 22 - New CADs to allow toggle of PID application for tilt and
                 focus. The two CADs are independent, i.e. you can apply
                 the tilt PID and NOT the focus PID, etc.
               - The default setting is that BOTH PIDs (tilt and focus) 
                 are ON
               - M2 status dm screen displays summed tilt+guide as total
                 demand
               - No longer using Rate Limit or Wind Up Limit in the PID
                 control alg. Just limiting M2 demands to not ask for more
                 than 100 um at a time.

SCS Version 21 - New CADs to drive offloaders, deployable baffles, central
                 baffle and XY positioner stepper motors individually
               - New info written to SCS from M2 via RM to indicate
                 initialization state and last recorded M2 error
               - Increased Z_GUIDE_STEP_LIMIT from 100 um to 500

SCS Version 20 - New CAD added to drive followers
               - Additions to checksum make it require 17jan2000 release
                 of M2 code.

SCS Version 19 - header files created for all files.
